<div id="cat_2" class="ui-tabs-panel ui-widget-content ui-corner-bottom" style=""><h2>General Questions</h2><br><p><i>Please answer the following general questions as accurately as possible for the best results. You may click on “View Benefit Results” at any time while answering these questions. The more questions you answer, the more likely you are to be eligible for the benefit programs that appear in your results list.</i></p><div id="cat_2_2081" class="ui-question"><div id="qid_2081" class="ui-question-text"><span style="float:left;line-height:25px;"><span style="float:left;"><strong style="float:left;line-height:25px;">1</strong>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Choose the option that best describes where you live:</span><span class="ui-icon-question-help" id="cat_2_qh_2081"></span></span></div><div title="Question Help Text" id="cat_2_help_2081" class="ui-question-help-content" style="display: none;"><p></p><p>Your response to this question will help us determine if you could get SSI. People who are in a jail or correctional facility cannot get SSI. People who live in a nursing home where Medicaid pays the cost could get SSI if their income is less than $30 per month. </p>
